&lt;ul type=&quot;disc&quot; style=&quot;direction:ltr;unicode-bidi:embed;margin-top:0in;
 margin-bottom:0in&quot;&gt;
 &lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 7pt;&quot;&gt;The proposal, by reason of siting and scale, would be an
     undesirable addition which would cause an undue loss of
     daylight, sunlight, outlook and privacy to neighbouring dwellings, resulting in a harmful impact to the amenity currently enjoyed by
     neighbouring occupiers. As such, the proposal fails to protect residential amenity
     and constitutes un-neighbourly development. It thus fails to
     accord with the following policies which seek to ensure that development
     proposals protect residential amenity:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 7pt;&quot;&gt;Paragraph 130 of the National Planning Policy
     Framework&amp;nbsp;National Planning Policy Framework (NPPF) (DLUHC, 2021)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 7pt;&quot;&gt;Policy D6 of the London Plan (March 2021)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 7pt;&quot;&gt;Policies&amp;nbsp;BP8 and BP11 of the&amp;nbsp;Local Development
     Framework (LDF) Borough Wide Development Plan Document (DPD) (March 2011)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 7pt;&quot;&gt;Sections 4.2, 5.3 and 5.4 of the Residential Extensions and
     Alterations Supplementary Planning Document (February 2012)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 7pt;&quot;&gt;Policies DMD1 and DMD6 of&amp;nbsp;The London Borough of Barking
     and Dagenham’s Draft Local Plan: (Regulation 19 Submission Version,
     December 2021)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul type=&quot;disc&quot; style=&quot;direction:ltr;unicode-bidi:embed;margin-top:0in;
 margin-bottom:0in&quot;&gt;
 
 
 
 
 &lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul type=&quot;disc&quot; style=&quot;direction:ltr;unicode-bidi:embed;margin-top:0in;
 margin-bottom:0in&quot;&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt;&quot;&gt;The
proposal, by reason of siting, mass, scale and design, would be an
undesirable addition which would appear as a bulky addition, disrupt the symmetry of the semi-detached pair, fail to appear subordinate to the original dwelling, constitute overdevelopment of
the site and introduce an incongruent roof form. As such, it fails to respect or reflect the appearance of the original
dwelling, the built form and rhythm of the street, and the character of the surrounding area,
causing harm to each of these.&amp;nbsp;The proposal thus fails to accord with the
following policies which seek to ensure development proposals are well
designed and respect and reflect existing character and appearance:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;ul type=&quot;disc&quot; style=&quot;direction:ltr;unicode-bidi:embed;margin-top:0in;
 margin-bottom:0in&quot;&gt;
 &lt;li style=&quot;margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;vertical-align:middle;margin-top:0pt;
     margin-bottom:8pt&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt&quot;&gt;Paragraph
     130 of the National Planning Policy Framework&amp;nbsp;National Planning
     Policy Framework (NPPF) (DLUHC, 2021)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
 &lt;li style=&quot;margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;vertical-align:middle;margin-top:0pt;
     margin-bottom:8pt&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt&quot;&gt;Policy&amp;nbsp;D4&amp;nbsp;of
     the London Plan (March 2021)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
 &lt;li style=&quot;margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;vertical-align:middle;margin-top:0pt;
     margin-bottom:8pt&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt&quot;&gt;Policies
     CP2 and CP3 of the&amp;nbsp;Local Development Framework (LDF) Core Strategy
     (July 2010)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
 &lt;li style=&quot;margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;vertical-align:middle;margin-top:0pt;
